{"TopicId":223479,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Kerbals are Twerking in shallow water","CreatedByName":"Robin Patenall","CreatedById":210278,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-03T23:04:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Robin Patenall","CreatedById":210278,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-03T23:04:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 (64 bit) | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 9 5900X 12-Core Processor | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E65450 Mb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLow priority issue that Kerbals (or at least Bob) appear to twerk when in shallow water.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFlew simple rocket West from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and splashed down in shallow water (in beach region)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nEVA\u0027d kerbal and took crew report and surface sample (splashed down / beach)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSwam to water line to repeat science on dry land\u00A0(landed\u00A0/ beach)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nKerbal stood up when water was shallow (knee to waist height)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nWhen not controlling kerbal, it would perform squats / twerk\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nProbably cycling between \u0022I\u0027m in water so I\u00A0need to switch to swim mode\u0022 and \u0022The water is too shallow so I need to switch to walk mode\u0022\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nWalking to dry land or deeper water\u00A0stopped the issue\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I\u0027d expect:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe kerbal to make up it\u0027s mind whether it needs to swim or stand\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSituational music to be added that the kerbals can dance to.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=KSP2Bug1.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BV/HYHtZ2XjqE7KPEJ/Hpf4U4ff2MdMNwnekMk9uVYnZ7Ay63QzmrKvUTuVbqnuQgTv0MV2DtCRUaWlUpta8nQrc=%5D%5B90644ba51d8a51fc4af37bea%5D%5B8d4c066c5fcd39766734051436b0b142%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKSP2Bug1.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-04T17:16:13Z\u0022 title=\u002202/04/2024 05:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 4\u0022\u003EFebruary 4\u003C/time\u003E by DibzNr\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Darta01","CreatedById":232639,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-16T18:31:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSituational music seems to be the most reasonable fix haha!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Little 908","CreatedById":228185,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-17T17:14:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncan we have like photo or video evidence?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnvm i missed the link\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-17T17:14